      <td>Global (default)</td>
      <td>Clients can access the endpoint using the IP address of any Gateway\nNode or Admin Node, the virtual IP (VIP) address of any HA group on any\nnetwork, or a corresponding FQDN.\nUse the Global setting (default) unless you need to restrict the accessibility\nof this endpoint.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <th>2</th>
      <td>Virtual IPs of HA groups</td>
      <td>Clients must use a virtual IP address (or corresponding FQDN) of an HA\ngroup to access this endpoint.\nEndpoints with this binding mode can all use the same port number, as\nlong as the HA groups you select for the endpoints donâ€™t overlap.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <th>3</th>
      <td>Node interfaces</td>
      <td>Clients must use the IP addresses (or corresponding FQDNs) of selected\nnode interfaces to access this endpoint.</td>
